Tue Jul 14 11:41:22 UTC 2026 - Martin Pluskal <mpluskal@suse.com>

- Update to 0.10.3:
  * Fix a cross-tenant data leak where auto-batch run processing
    could drop a request's workspace override and send runs to the
    wrong workspace
  * Raise the minimum supported LangSmith backend to 0.16.13rc1
  * Capture realtime/TTS model costs for the optional LiveKit and
    Pipecat voice integrations (extras not enabled in this package)
- Security references for tracking (already fixed in this package; not
  newly fixed by 0.10.3, verified while updating):
  * CVE-2026-45134 (boo#1266666): the prompt-pull methods deserialized
    attacker-controlled prompt manifests (serialized LangChain objects
    and model configuration); fixed upstream in langsmith 0.8.0 and
    shipped here since 0.9.3
  * CVE-2026-41182 (boo#1262699): output redaction (hide_outputs) was
    not applied to streaming token events, leaking streamed content;
    fixed upstream in langsmith 0.7.31 and shipped here since 0.9.3
  * CVE-2026-40190 (boo#1262017): prototype pollution in a vendored
    lodash set() helper affects only the JavaScript/TypeScript SDK
    (Node.js); this Python package does not ship that code and is not
    affected

